TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi sealed NetworkInterfaceType extends System.Enum

Docs.summary: Specifies types of network interfaces.

remarks.format:
## Remarks Network interfaces, also known as network adapters, connect a computer to a network. The interface type defines the transmission media that provides network connectivity.
This enumeration defines the values returned by the <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterface.NetworkInterfaceType%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType AsymmetricDsl = int32(94)
AsymmetricDsl = 94

Docs.summary: The network interface uses an Asymmetric Digital Subscriber Line (ADSL).

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Atm = int32(37)
Atm = 37

Docs.summary: The network interface uses asynchronous transfer mode (ATM) for data transmission.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType BasicIsdn = int32(20)
BasicIsdn = 20

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a basic rate interface Integrated Services Digital Network (ISDN) connection. ISDN is a set of standards for data transmission over telephone lines.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Ethernet = int32(6)
Ethernet = 6

Docs.summary: The network interface uses an Ethernet connection. Ethernet is defined in IEEE standard 802.3.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Ethernet3Megabit = int32(26)
Ethernet3Megabit = 26

Docs.summary: The network interface uses an Ethernet 3 megabit/second connection. This version of Ethernet is defined in IETF RFC 895.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType FastEthernetFx = int32(69)
FastEthernetFx = 69

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Fast Ethernet connection over optical fiber and provides a data rate of 100 megabits per second. This type of connection is also known as 100Base-FX.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType FastEthernetT = int32(62)
FastEthernetT = 62

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Fast Ethernet connection over twisted pair and provides a data rate of 100 megabits per second. This type of connection is also known as 100Base-T.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Fddi = int32(15)
Fddi = 15

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Fiber Distributed Data Interface (FDDI) connection. FDDI is a set of standards for data transmission on fiber optic lines in a local area network.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType GenericModem = int32(48)
GenericModem = 48

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a modem.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType GigabitEthernet = int32(117)
GigabitEthernet = 117

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a gigabit Ethernet connection and provides a data rate of 1,000 megabits per second (1 gigabit per second).

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType HighPerformanceSerialBus = int32(144)
HighPerformanceSerialBus = 144

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a High Performance Serial Bus.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType IPOverAtm = int32(114)
IPOverAtm = 114

Docs.summary: The network interface uses the Internet Protocol (IP) in combination with asynchronous transfer mode (ATM) for data transmission.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Isdn = int32(63)
Isdn = 63

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a connection configured for ISDN and the X.25 protocol. X.25 allows computers on public networks to communicate using an intermediary computer.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Loopback = int32(24)
Loopback = 24

Docs.summary: The network interface is a loopback adapter. Such interfaces are often used for testing; no traffic is sent over the wire.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType MultiRateSymmetricDsl = int32(143)
MultiRateSymmetricDsl = 143

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Multirate Digital Subscriber Line.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Ppp = int32(23)
Ppp = 23

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Point-To-Point protocol (PPP) connection. PPP is a protocol for data transmission using a serial device.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType PrimaryIsdn = int32(21)
PrimaryIsdn = 21

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a primary rate interface Integrated Services Digital Network (ISDN) connection. ISDN is a set of standards for data transmission over telephone lines.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType RateAdaptDsl = int32(95)
RateAdaptDsl = 95

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Rate Adaptive Digital Subscriber Line (RADSL).

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Slip = int32(28)
Slip = 28

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Serial Line Internet Protocol (SLIP) connection. SLIP is defined in IETF RFC 1055.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType SymmetricDsl = int32(96)
SymmetricDsl = 96

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Symmetric Digital Subscriber Line (SDSL).

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType TokenRing = int32(9)
TokenRing = 9

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Token-Ring connection. Token-Ring is defined in IEEE standard 802.5.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Tunnel = int32(131)
Tunnel = 131

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a tunnel connection.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Unknown = int32(1)
Unknown = 1

Docs.summary: The interface type is not known.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType VeryHighSpeedDsl = int32(97)
VeryHighSpeedDsl = 97

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a Very High Data Rate Digital Subscriber Line (VDSL).

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Wireless80211 = int32(71)
Wireless80211 = 71

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a wireless LAN connection (IEEE 802.11 standard).

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Wman = int32(237)
Wman = 237

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a mobile broadband interface for WiMax devices.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Wwanpp = int32(243)
Wwanpp = 243

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a mobile broadband interface for GSM-based devices.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkInterfaceType Wwanpp2 = int32(244)
Wwanpp2 = 244

Docs.summary: The network interface uses a mobile broadband interface for CDMA-based devices.
